-- Monaco Will Offer Rooney Tax-Free Wage Deal, Star Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-03-13T10:31:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-13/monaco-will-offer-rooney-tax-free-wage-deal-star-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
web.  Monaco Haven  Monaco wants to mark its return to France’s Ligue 1 by
signing  Manchester United  striker  Wayne Rooney , the  Daily Star 
reported.  Monaco officials say they are prepared to “blow their
rivals out of the water” with the size of its bid and tax-free
wage offer, according to the Star.  Cristiano Stays  Cristiano Ronaldo’s agent Jorge Mendes has told the former
world player of the year to stay at Real Madrid one more season,
the  Daily Mail  reported.  Ronaldo has two years left on his contract and is
considering leaving  Spain  for Paris Saint-Germain or Manchester
United, according to the Mail.  Reading Coach  Gus Poyet is a contender to manage Reading, which fired
Brian McDermott with nine Premier League games remaining, the
 Daily Mail  reported.  Poyet is chasing a play-off spot as Brighton coach, the
Mail said.  Zigic Out  Birmingham is seeking to trade Nikola Zigic as the
striker’s contract terms push up his salary, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  Zigic’s weekly pay will rise to 62,000 pounds ($92,700)
next season from 50,000 pounds when the Blues were relegated
from the Premier League in 2011, the Mirror said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
